<div class="ui text container">
  <h2 class="ui header">Ember + Lux boilerplate</h2>
  <div class="ui segment">
    <p>
      This app serves as basic boilerplate for an <b>Ember</b> + <b>Lux</b> application.
    </p>
    <h3>Authentication</h3>
    <p>
      Basic authentication via JWT is provided. By default a token is valid for 30 minutes or 7 days when &quot;remember me&quot; is ticked on login. These values can be customized in <code>server/app/utils/constants</code>.
    </p>
    <h3>Models</h3>
    <p>
      A single <code>User</code> model with basic attributes is present in both the server and the client.
    </p>
    <h3>Semantic UI</h3>
    <p>
      Semantic UI is available in this package. It is only partially imported by default. You can change which components you want to import in <code>app/styles/semantic-ui.less</code>.
    </p>
    <h4 class="ui dividing header"></h4>
    {{#if session.isAuthenticated}}
      <p>
        You are now logged in <i>{{sessionAccount.user.firstName}}</i>!
      </p>
    {{else}}
      <p>
        You can <b>login</b> in the top right corner.
      </p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
</div>